## рџ“Љ CORE FEATURES (BUILD IN ORDER)

### Phase 1 вЂ” Foundation
1. Channel URL input (parse @handle, /channel/, /c/ formats)
2. YouTube API proxy route
3. Fetch channel info + video list
4. Basic video grid with thumbnail, title, views, date

### Phase 2 вЂ” Analytics Engine
5. Engagement Rate = `(likes + comments) / views * 100`
6. Performance Score (0-100) = weighted composite:
   - 40% views (normalized vs channel avg)
   - 35% engagement rate
   - 25% recency bonus
7. Trend Velocity = views last 30d vs prev 30d (% delta)
8. Sort: Views, Engagement, Score, Date, Duration
9. Filter: date range, min views, video type

### Phase 3 вЂ” Charts
10. Views over time (LineChart вЂ” last 20 videos)
11. Top 10 by views (BarChart)
12. Engagement distribution (BarChart)
13. Channel stats overview (4 KPI cards)

### Phase 4 вЂ” Polish
14. CSV export (all metrics)
15. "Best Performer" badge on top 3 videos
16. Trending up/down indicator per video
17. Click video в†’ opens YouTube in new tab
18. Mobile responsive

## рџ”§ YOUTUBE API USAGE

### Endpoints:
```typescript
// Channel lookup
GET /youtube/v3/channels?part=snippet,statistics&forHandle={handle}&key=KEY

// Videos via uploads playlist
GET /youtube/v3/playlistItems?part=snippet&playlistId={uploadsId}&maxResults=50&key=KEY

// Batch video stats
GET /youtube/v3/videos?part=snippet,statistics,contentDetails&id={ids}&key=KEY
```

### URL Parsing вЂ” handle ALL formats:
```typescript
// https://www.youtube.com/@MrBeast
// https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCX6OQ3DkcsbYNE6H8uQQuVA
// https://www.youtube.com/c/MrBeast6000
// @MrBeast (bare handle)
// MrBeast (just name)
```

### CRITICAL: API key is ALWAYS server-side
- Route: `/app/api/youtube/route.ts`
- Env var: `YOUTUBE_API_KEY`
- Client never touches the key

